summary: What do you think the GHC's favorite Disney princess movies are?
question: What do you think the GHC's favorite Disney princess movies are?
answer:
buffy’s is either mulan or brave because they’re about choosing your own path and the women are badass and they’re amazing

cyrus’s is beauty and the beast (i had a gut feeling about this one) because cyrus loves the songs. hell, he was probably in a class production of beauty and the beast at one point. he’s really excited when he hears that a gay character is going to be in the reboot and he just loves the story. 

andi’s is (and this may just be me projecting here) little mermaid. andi loves the music and the aesthetic. i can imagine her going through a mermaid phase and cece and ham having to fight over who has to tell her that mermaids aren’t real and andi’s slightly heartbroken but she deals with it. andi loves all disney princesses movies though, a little bit much, and thus her huge want for a boyfriend

summary: Ok I’ve seen the Millicent’s character is actually Jonah’s sister theory floating around and I don’t really buy it. Not cause...
body: Ok I’ve seen the Millicent’s character is actually Jonah’s sister theory floating around and I don’t really buy it. Not cause it’s a reveal that would come completely out of no where with no buildup since after 2B I wouldn’t put it past the show to do that. No, for me it’s the way Jonah interacts with her character in that brief clip. Look, I can’t speak for you guys, but personally having an older brother close in age to me he has never gently caressed my face and push my hair behind my ear. And it’s not something he would do, and I really don’t know how the show would be able to come up with a non awkward explanation for that behavior if they went with this reveal.
